parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty heater core can cause the windshield to fog up, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, it can lead to water leakage and damage to the vehicle's electrical system.
symptoms: Windshield fogging
poor visibility
water leakage
and malfunctioning of the defroster system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning windshield wiper motor can leave the wipers stuck in the middle of the windshield, obstructing the driver's view and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stuck in the middle of the windshield
malfunctioning wiper motor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to engine components, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: The temperature gauge is in the red zone
the engine is making a loud knocking or grinding noise
the coolant light is illuminated
steam is coming from the hood
the vehicle is losing power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or decelerate, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control is not engaging
the cruise control is not disengaging
the vehicle is suddenly accelerating or decelerating
the cruise control light is flashing or illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper installation of the catalytic converter can cause damage to the distributor cap and catalytic converter, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle is experiencing poor engine performance
the vehicle is producing excessive exhaust smoke
the distributor cap is damaged or blown.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative front seat belts can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The front seat belts do not function
the front seat belts do not latch or unlatch
the front seat belts are stuck
the front seat belts do not retract properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can cause a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brakes lose effectiveness intermittently
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brakes fail to respond when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A hard brake pedal can cause a delay in stopping the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or difficult to press
the brakes require excessive force to stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
